latestIgtvVideos.title: Acting Audition from 2019 at @mukeshchhabracc
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I was told to play the character of a Pregnant Woman who just had a miscarriage and she lost her baby. Phone calling her husband who is at work and telling him about the same . 

Not many know this, but Having done theatre for 3 Years I always wanted to persue Acting as a career and giving it a chance . 

I wasn't confident much sharing my audition clips here on social media . ( having my own insecurities) . However, this Passion was a part of me and I will always love Cinema no matter what. If you know me personally and my work Professionally, I always try to put an element of Cinema in my work . 
Be it my current passion @yourminestory 
The element of Cinema will always be Visible . 

To portray something you haven't experienced just depends on Believing and Imagining . 
Having Believing the scene truly with all my heart, I still remember the feeling of a mother loosing a child . This is so absurd yet true . 
@maheshbalraj @shreedhardubey 
Thank you for all the Learnings 🌟
.

I do miss Acting ! However, @yourminestory has all my heart now .

.

latestIgtvVideos.title: NEHA SOOD X THE ATTIC LIFE
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Messed up Wardrobe and No Time to organise it ? Let me introduce you all,  @the.atticlife ,  Professional organising clutter management and Home staging company . 
Due to regular Shoots I literally had no time to set my wardrobe,  segregate the unwanted clothes and organised it in proper way! And it’s even more Bad when Mom’s away :( . Thanks to @the.atticlife for helping me organise my wardrobe in such a beautiful way . She managed all by herself and All I had to do was tell her the Category of clothing to be set together . My Life made so easy ❤️. .
CHECK OUT THE ENTIRE VIDEO AND SEE THE OUTCOME 😍
.
My wardrobe had so much more space 😂 , I actually felt empty 👀! Finally I Can add some Stuff ❤️.
.
If you want to avail this service , You may directly connect with @the.atticlife 😊❤️ for more details :) .
